transcription.text: This is Robin. Hey, Robin. My name is James. Karen has been a client for, I don't know, like 11 years now. I just noticed when I go to PCR capture, if I'm on LinkedIn, actually, I've noticed this for a while now. But when I go there and I go to candidate and you know how you can like put them into PCR from there. If they're already in my database, and sometimes even if not, it won't let me choose their current company on LinkedIn. It used to do that. Are you familiar with this? Yeah, it could be just a setting at the top. When you click on the extension at the top right of your browser, that's going to pop up all the links or sites that it supports. At the very bottom right, is basic mode off? Like, is it showing gray or blue? Okay. Sorry. One second. So if I go to – I couldn't see what you were talking about. Okay. Yeah, because it's probably a setting. Yep. Okay. Okay, capture. Okay, and then it says basic mode is not on. Capture to default company is what it says right now. Okay, is that on? That's on. Capture to default company is on. If you turn that off so it's gray, like usually you want all of those gray. If you slide that so it's gray, what that will do is let you either create or pick a company. Otherwise, it's trying to put everybody into your default company. Okay, that's extremely helpful. So now you should, and you'll want to definitely watch when you have that capture to default company off. If the company is already found in your database as an exact match, hover on that card and use the checkbox. So that way you're not making any changes to the company by what it's reading from the profile. You're just picking it and adding the person into that company. Got it. Okay. All right. Perfect. Perfect. Okay. That worked. Thank you so much. You are very welcome. That's really helpful. Have a great week. You too. Thank you. Bye-bye.
